that I'm not grateful,

6
00:01:40,100 --> 00:01:43,270
I mean, I mean to my bones

7
00:01:44,539 --> 00:01:46,473
about how my life turned around.

8
00:01:53,180 --> 00:01:54,281
- Shoot.

9
00:01:55,850 --> 00:01:58,753
We've been into some pretty
dark places together.

10
00:02:02,189 --> 00:02:03,290
I mean,

11
00:02:06,126 --> 00:02:07,595
you turned it around,

12
00:02:09,262 --> 00:02:10,898
made a life for yourself.

13
00:02:15,737 --> 00:02:18,305
I guess I just wanted to know

14
00:02:21,375 --> 00:02:23,176
how you did that?

15
00:02:28,650 --> 00:02:32,053
- You hear these rare stories, you know?

16
00:02:32,185 --> 00:02:33,855
Of how the impossible happened.

17
00:02:37,157 --> 00:02:38,258
Well,

18
00:02:39,727 --> 00:02:42,195
this is one of those stories.

19
00:03:13,528 --> 00:03:16,463
Hey!

20
00:03:49,997 --> 00:03:54,035
It was the 1950s, but if
you pulled up to our yard,

21
00:03:54,168 --> 00:03:56,838
you would've thought it was the 1850s.

22
00:03:56,971 --> 00:03:58,906
That's how poor we were.

23
00:03:59,040 --> 00:04:01,743
Dad spent most of his time
workin' in the oil fields.

24
00:04:01,876 --> 00:04:03,644
I wish you didn't always have to go.

25
00:04:03,778 --> 00:04:06,279
- Hell, that's life, Phil.

26
00:04:06,413 --> 00:04:07,849
It's time you grew up.

27
00:04:11,652 --> 00:04:13,521
Take care of things around here.

28
00:04:15,255 --> 00:04:15,957
You got it?

29
