You gotta be kiddin' me.

141
00:10:39,006 --> 00:10:40,474
- I seen the way he looks at you.

142
00:10:40,609 --> 00:10:42,643
- Hey, Phil
Robertson, can I get a statement?

143
00:10:43,477 --> 00:10:44,579
- Nah, nah.

144
00:10:44,712 --> 00:10:46,280
You wanna talk to Si Robertson right her

145
00:10:46,413 --> 00:10:47,549
Real hero of the game.

146
00:10:47,681 --> 00:10:48,617
- Si Robertson?

147
00:10:48,749 --> 00:10:50,351
Did you even play?

148
00:10:50,484 --> 00:10:51,952
- Boy, did I even play?

149
00:10:52,086 --> 00:10:53,721
I was so fast like lightning,

150
00:10:53,854 --> 00:10:54,922
that's why it probably didn't even feel

151
00:10:55,055 --> 00:10:56,690
like you saw me out there on that field.

152
00:10:56,824 --> 00:10:58,692
- Miss Kay Carroway.

153
00:10:58,826 --> 00:10:59,994
- Hey, Phil.

154
00:11:00,127 --> 00:11:00,828
- Hey.

155
00:11:01,695 --> 00:11:03,397
Look, I know we don't know
each other all that well,

156
00:11:03,532 --> 00:11:07,268
but think maybe I could walk
you off the field tonight?

157
00:11:07,401 --> 00:11:08,169
- I'd like that.

158
00:11:09,470 --> 00:11:10,471
- Okay.

159
00:11:10,605 --> 00:11:11,939
So we walked off the field together

160
00:11:12,072 --> 00:11:13,941
and she offered me a ride home.

161
00:11:14,609 --> 00:11:16,043
I didn't even have the luxury of goin'

162
00:11:16,177 --> 00:11:18,479
on my first date without
at least one third wheel.

163
00:11:18,613 --> 00:11:19,914
- And that's when I went down to pet

164
00:11:20,047 --> 00:11:22,551
what I thought was a
dog, and no way, okay?

165
00:11:22,683 --> 00:11:24,785
Turned out it was a five-pound squirrel.

166
00:11:24,919 --> 00:11:26,253
- Sorry about this.

167
00:11:26,387 --> 00:11:28,322
- I mean, I really do despise beavers,

168
00:11:28,455 --> 00:11:31,725
but I also respect their
work ethic and determination.

169
00:11:36,130 --> 00:11:37,364
- You're gonna stay in the car.

170
00:11:37,498 --> 00:11:39,634
- What do you mean?
- This is my date,

171
00:11:39,767 --> 00:11:40,834
so you're stayin'.

172
00:11:40,968 --> 00:11:42,504
- I'll be skin and bone if I don't eat.

173
00:11:42,637 --> 00:11:43,804
- I hate to break it to ya,
honey, but you already are.

174
00:11:43,938 --> 00:11:45,873
- Hey Jack, I am wastin' away.

175
00:11:46,006 --> 00:11:46,974
- All right, fine, fine.

176
00:11:47,107 --> 00:11:48,375
Quit your yappin'.

177
00:11:48,510 --> 00:11:49,376
I'll get you somethin',
but you're stayin' here.

178
00:11:49,511 --> 00:11:50,411
- All right.

179
00:11:53,881 --> 00:11:54,982
All right.

180
00:11:57,851 --> 00:11:59,453
- Sorry about that.

181
00:12:12,166 --> 00:12:13,434
- I know girls are supposed to act

182
00:12:13,568 --> 00:12:14,735
like they don't eat
nothin' on these dates,

183
00:12:14,868 --> 00:12:17,438
but I am absolutely starvin'.

184
00:12:17,572 --> 00:12:18,339
Hey, Rachel?

185
00:12:18,472 --> 00:12:19,873
- Hey, Kay.

186
00:12:20,007 --> 00:12:21,775
- Could I get two muffy
sandwiches and a large fry?

187
00:12:21,909 --> 00:12:22,810
What you want? I can pay.

188
00:12:22,943 --> 00:12:23,777
- Hey, no, come on.

189
00:12:23,911 --> 00:12:26,247
You drove, I got this.

190
00:12:29,216 --> 00:12:31,285
Uh, you know, I don't really
eat after the games anyway,

191
