201
00:12:53,040 --> 00:12:54,542
- Where is it?

202
00:12:54,676 --> 00:12:57,579
- When she was good, she was
great. Funny, sharp, kind.

203
00:12:57,712 --> 00:12:59,179
- Ma, what are you lookin' for?

204
00:12:59,313 --> 00:13:00,548
- The money.

205
00:13:00,682 --> 00:13:02,016
Where's the money?

206
00:13:02,149 --> 00:13:03,183
- I keep tellin' you,
we ain't got no money.

207
00:13:03,317 --> 00:13:05,587
At least not in the way you're sayin'.

208
00:13:05,720 --> 00:13:06,755
- Oh no, from your pa.

209
00:13:06,887 --> 00:13:08,055
He's been sendin' it.

210
00:13:08,188 --> 00:13:09,890
- But when it wasn't her day-

211
00:13:10,024 --> 00:13:11,225
- I got back
from the hospital and-

212
00:13:11,358 --> 00:13:13,260
- Life was hell for all of us.

213
00:13:13,394 --> 00:13:15,396
Yes, Mama, and Pa did send it.

214
00:13:15,530 --> 00:13:16,564
We've been usin' it.

215
00:13:16,698 --> 00:13:17,831
Jan needed actual clothes for school,

216
00:13:17,965 --> 00:13:20,000
Si needed shoes for football.

217
00:13:20,134 --> 00:13:22,537
Everything around us costs money.

218
00:13:26,006 --> 00:13:26,940
- Why are you wearing that?

219
00:13:27,074 --> 00:13:28,375
Why are you all dressed up?

220
00:13:30,679 --> 00:13:32,580
- 'Cause I got a date tonight.

221
00:13:33,947 --> 00:13:35,916
- You got a date?

222
00:13:36,050 --> 00:13:38,553
Oh, baby, with who, huh?

223
00:13:41,121 --> 00:13:42,557
- Kay Carroway.

224
00:13:46,427 --> 00:13:47,394
- Carroway?

225
00:13:49,764 --> 00:13:52,066
That rich family in town?

226
