- This is as fresh as it
comes, Appaloosa catfish.

530
00:32:13,835 --> 00:32:15,969
That's the filet mignon of the river.

531
00:32:16,937 --> 00:32:19,072
- Jan!
- Hi, Kay.

532
00:32:19,206 --> 00:32:20,974
- It's good to see you, sweetheart

533
00:32:21,108 --> 00:32:22,376
- Hey, Phil.
- Hey, Jan.

534
00:32:22,510 --> 00:32:23,578
- How you doin'?

535
00:32:23,711 --> 00:32:24,679
- I'm good, how are you?
- It's good to see you.

536
00:32:24,813 --> 00:32:25,946
- You too.

537
00:32:26,079 --> 00:32:26,881
- Hey, hey, how you doin'?
- Hey.

538
00:32:27,014 --> 00:32:27,981
- I'm Al.

539
00:32:28,115 --> 00:32:30,585
You must be one of Kay's friends.

540
00:32:30,718 --> 00:32:33,220
I know Phil ain't got
no good lookin' friends.

541
00:32:33,353 --> 00:32:35,222
Well, except for me, of course.

542
00:32:36,791 --> 00:32:37,525
- That's my sister.

543
00:32:39,259 --> 00:32:40,994
- Okay, okay.

544
00:32:41,128 --> 00:32:42,429
Oh, yeah, okay.

545
00:32:42,564 --> 00:32:43,330
All right.

546
00:32:43,464 --> 00:32:45,365
I mean, I was just bein' friendly.

547
00:32:45,499 --> 00:32:46,668
- Why don't you be friendly

548
00:32:46,801 --> 00:32:49,136
in that direction over there, Al?

549
00:32:50,003 --> 00:32:51,104
- Okay.

550
00:32:52,072 --> 00:32:53,842
- Sorry about him.
- No, I'm good.

551
00:32:53,974 --> 00:32:55,910
Hey, congratulations on your new job.

552
00:32:56,043 --> 00:32:57,044
I'm so proud of you.

553
00:32:57,177 --> 00:32:58,412
- Thanks, Jan.

554
00:32:58,546 --> 00:33:00,280
- Did Kay tell you we took the boys

555
00:33:00,414 --> 00:33:01,850
to church last weekend?

556
00:33:01,982 --> 00:33:02,951
They seemed to really enjoy it.

557
00:33:03,083 --> 00:33:05,018
You should come with us next time.

558
00:33:05,854 --> 00:33:08,121
- Yeah, well, I like to spend

559
00:33:08,255 --> 00:33:10,859
my Sunday celebratin' God in other ways.

560
00:33:11,626 --> 00:33:15,864
Who needs a pew when you
can be out in His creation?

561
00:33:15,996 --> 00:33:18,733
- Hey, y'all, how 'bout a toast, huh?

562
00:33:19,968 --> 00:33:21,603
To my man Phil Robertson here,

563
00:33:21,736 --> 00:33:26,574
the newest remedial English
teacher at Junction City High.

564
00:33:27,174 --> 00:33:29,042
He ain't smart but he pretty.

565
00:33:31,278 --> 00:33:33,080
- I can't do, I can't deal.

566
00:33:33,213 --> 00:33:35,048
- Four ducks?
- Yeah, four ducks.

567
00:33:35,182 --> 00:33:36,216
- Four ducks.

568
00:33:36,350 --> 00:33:37,384
One bullet can't take down four ducks.

569
00:33:37,519 --> 00:33:38,953
- Oh, it can if you're Phil Robertson.

570
00:33:39,086 --> 00:33:40,855
- Who's this new friend with him?

571
00:33:40,989 --> 00:33:42,590
- That's Al.

572
00:33:44,458 --> 00:33:46,260
He's from his work.

573
00:33:46,393 --> 00:33:48,228
He runs their school.
- Oh, okay.

574
00:33:49,463 --> 00:33:50,665
- Yeah, it's that easy.

575
00:33:51,331 --> 00:33:53,033
- Woo ee!
- Woo!

576
00:33:55,737 --> 00:33:56,303
- Ow!

577
00:34:02,844 --> 00:34:04,444
Woo!
- Told you boys.

578
00:34:04,579 --> 00:34:07,682
One thing I'm better at
than fishin' is shootin'.

579
00:34:08,583 --> 00:34:09,383
- You okay?

580
00:34:09,517 --> 00:34:10,585
- Yeah.
- This here

581
00:34:10,718 --> 00:34:14,288
is some genuine Three Creeks moonshine.

582
00:34:16,024 --> 00:34:16,925
- All right.

583
00:34:28,636 --> 00:34:29,537
- Daddy?

584
00:34:31,906 --> 00:34:33,206
You goin' huntin'?

585
00:34:33,942 --> 00:34:35,142
- You bet ya.

586
00:34:36,744 --> 00:34:37,645
- Can I come?

587
00:34:39,647 --> 00:34:41,381
- You don't know the woods.

588
00:34:42,115 --> 00:34:43,985
You don't know huntin'.

589
00:34:44,117 --> 00:34:46,588
- You could teach me.

590
00:34:54,127 --> 00:34:55,597
- Go back to bed.

591
00:35:01,069 --> 00:35:04,271
The next few years were a
bit of a blur, I must admit.

592
00:35:11,579 --> 00:35:13,413
- You said you know the guy
that owns this property?

593
00:35:13,548 --> 00:35:15,349
- Yeah, I met him once.

594
00:35:15,482 --> 00:35:16,651
- Well, I met his sister.

595
00:35:21,455 --> 00:35:23,457
- It was that feeling again,

596
00:35:23,591 --> 00:35:25,693
being pulled in multiple directions.

597
00:35:27,895 --> 00:35:29,931
Huntin', partying, family.

598
00:35:30,064 --> 00:35:33,333
The drinkin' began to
overtake everything else.

599
00:35:33,467 --> 00:35:37,371
"Airplanes follow duck."

600
00:35:40,775 --> 00:35:42,777
I thought it was freedom to my worries,

601
00:35:43,511 --> 00:35:45,445
but it didn't free me from 'em.

602
00:35:45,580 --> 00:35:48,082
It just made me forget about them.

603
00:36:06,601 --> 00:36:09,604
She just will not leave me alone.

604
00:36:11,204 --> 00:36:13,975
- I've heard of worse problems than that

605
00:36:14,108 --> 00:36:15,076
And all I could think was,

606
00:36:15,208 --> 00:36:17,111
"Man, I gotta lay off the sauce."

607
00:36:18,445 --> 00:36:19,446
- They respected Phil Robertson.

608
00:36:19,580 --> 00:36:22,215
They know Phil Robertson was a man.

609
00:36:22,349 --> 00:36:23,417
Who's a man?

610
00:36:28,589 --> 00:36:30,892
You're so beautiful, Marleen.

611
00:36:43,805 --> 00:36:46,674
- You wasn't
callin' them ducks in, Phil.

612
00:36:46,808 --> 00:36:49,911
You was commandin' them to come in.

613
00:36:50,778 --> 00:36:51,979
- Back again?

614
00:36:52,113 --> 00:36:53,480
You don't even have the
decency to hang around here?

615
00:36:53,614 --> 00:36:54,549
I'm cookin' you dinner,

616
00:36:54,682 --> 00:36:55,850
I'm cleanin' up after the kids-

617
00:36:55,983 --> 00:36:58,351
- Keep your mouth shut!

618
00:36:58,485 --> 00:37:00,353
- What, you can't even have
a conversation with me?

619
00:37:07,061 --> 00:37:08,029
- Y'all don't need this.

620
00:37:10,198 --> 00:37:12,066
Class dismissed.

621
00:37:20,541 --> 00:37:22,342
- Who's a man?

622
00:37:27,115 --> 00:37:30,250
- I was hell-bent
on doin' things my own way.

623
00:37:31,052 --> 00:37:32,019
I always had been.

624
00:37:35,656 --> 00:37:37,125
So, when I had to figure out other ways

625
00:37:37,257 --> 00:37:38,793
to provide for the family,

626
00:37:38,926 --> 00:37:41,963
I went back to the places
that have always provided,

627
00:37:42,096 --> 00:37:44,165
the woods, and the river.

628
00:38:04,417 --> 00:38:06,453
- Take care.
- Oh.

629
00:38:08,189 --> 00:38:10,558
- Miss Abaleen.

630
00:38:12,059 --> 00:38:14,095
- Phil Robertson.

631
00:38:14,228 --> 00:38:15,295
You been stayin' outta trouble?

632
00:38:15,428 --> 00:38:16,564
- Yes, Ma'am.

633
00:38:16,697 --> 00:38:17,865
- How's your mama?

634
00:38:21,068 --> 00:38:21,869
- She doin' just great.

635
00:38:22,003 --> 00:38:23,738
- Kay and the kids?

636
00:38:23,871 --> 00:38:24,806
- It's all good.

637
00:38:24,939 --> 00:38:25,840
Hey?

638
00:38:26,707 --> 00:38:28,408
Got a fresh catch for ya.

639
00:38:28,543 --> 00:38:30,144
- You back on the water?

640
00:38:30,278 --> 00:38:31,411
I thought I heard you teachin' down

641
00:38:31,546 --> 00:38:33,247
at that school in Junction City?

642
00:38:33,380 --> 00:38:35,348
- Yeah, yeah.

643
00:38:38,052 --> 00:38:40,387
Sabbatical, you know?

644
00:38:41,289 --> 00:38:42,890
Just a short break.

645
00:38:44,058 --> 00:38:45,760
- I got myself plenty for the shop today

646
00:38:45,893 --> 00:38:48,863
You know I don't like
throwin' out no unsold fish.

647
00:38:49,597 --> 00:38:51,398
- This here's as fresh as it comes.

648
00:38:51,532 --> 00:38:54,367
You could put this on
special right up front.

649
00:38:57,505 --> 00:38:59,406
Caught no more than an hour ago.

650
00:39:03,244 --> 00:39:04,645
Have a look.

651
00:39:05,445 --> 00:39:06,814
- Mm hm.

652
00:39:19,794 --> 00:39:20,628
- I appreciate you-

653
00:39:20,761 --> 00:39:22,230
- Mm hm.

654
00:39:22,362 --> 00:39:24,999
- You best make sure Miss
Kay and the boys get this.

655
00:39:25,132 --> 00:39:26,100
- Yes, Ma'am.

656
00:39:26,234 --> 00:39:27,400
Absolutely.

657
00:39:36,277 --> 00:39:37,377
Do.

658
00:39:38,746 --> 00:39:40,882
I'm ashamed to say most of that money

659
00:39:41,015 --> 00:39:43,684
I was makin' didn't go
to Kay and the kids,

660
00:39:43,818 --> 00:39:46,020
but we always found a way to make more.

661
00:39:49,790 --> 00:39:53,895
Hey, if nothin' else, we were creative.

662
00:39:54,962 --> 00:39:57,798
- All right, y'all, all bets are in.

663
00:39:57,932 --> 00:40:01,002
Got a rivalry as old as time.

664
00:40:02,036 --> 00:40:05,039
Man versus machine!

665
00:40:05,172 --> 00:40:06,941
Steel versus muscle!

666
00:40:08,441 --> 00:40:11,212
Rubber versus some bare feet.

667
00:40:11,345 --> 00:40:13,915
- Mm hm!
- Yeah, Phil!

668
00:40:14,048 --> 00:40:16,717
- All right.
- Let's go, come on!

669
00:40:16,851 --> 00:40:18,219
- Let's get
this show on the boat!

670
00:40:20,321 --> 00:40:21,689
- Come on, Phil!

671
00:40:23,190 --> 00:40:26,627
- On your mark,
- You got this, buddy!

672
00:40:29,363 --> 00:40:30,364
- get set,

673
00:40:34,001 --> 00:40:34,869
go!

674
00:40:42,376 --> 00:40:43,911
- What you doin' there?

675
00:40:44,045 --> 00:40:44,912
- Woo!

676
00:40:47,848 --> 00:40:49,784
- Just like old times, gentlemen.

677
00:40:50,518 --> 00:40:53,554
Don't give me that sour look
like I'm tryin' to cheat ya.

678
00:40:53,688 --> 00:40:55,823
It's Hank's car and he bet against me.

679
00:40:55,957 --> 00:40:58,025
You think he hamstrung his own bet?

680
00:40:58,726 --> 00:41:01,295
Hey, come on, now, pay up.

681
00:41:01,429 --> 00:41:02,897
Fair and square.

682
00:41:03,597 --> 00:41:06,567
Hey, don't be bitter.

683
00:41:06,701 --> 00:41:07,935
You and I both know Hank's car

684
00:41:08,069 --> 00:41:09,637
ain't got the gun to come even close

685
00:41:09,770 --> 00:41:12,573
to outrunnin' you if you
only give him 20 yards.

686
00:41:13,473 --> 00:41:17,044
You give him 25, he's got you smoked.

687
00:41:18,746 --> 00:41:23,684
- Well, that's their fault
for not askin' for 25.

688
00:41:26,787 --> 00:41:27,755
- Man, ever since I known you,

689
00:41:27,888 --> 00:41:29,190
you ain't never changed.

690
00:41:29,323 --> 00:41:30,624
- Hey, Phil?

691
00:41:30,758 --> 00:41:32,259
Double or nothin'.

692
00:41:34,061 --> 00:41:35,563
- Hold my beer.

693
00:41:44,739 --> 00:41:46,240
Hey, Babe.

694
00:41:48,743 --> 00:41:51,545
- Guess you decided to finally come home

695
00:41:52,413 --> 00:41:54,248
- I know it's late, I was...

696
00:41:55,316 --> 00:41:57,084
I was, uh,

697
00:41:58,352 --> 00:42:00,187
workin'.

698
00:42:01,255 --> 00:42:03,124
- Sell some fish?

699
00:42:03,257 --> 00:42:04,658
- Yep.

700
00:42:13,167 --> 00:42:14,835
- What is this?

701
00:42:15,703 --> 00:42:17,905
- That's money I made.

702
00:42:18,039 --> 00:42:20,541
- Well, how much fish you sell?

703
00:42:20,674 --> 00:42:21,942
- What do you mean?

704
00:42:22,710 --> 00:42:24,945
- There's $11 here.

705
00:42:27,081 --> 00:42:31,719
- I know, I musta spent
some of it, all right?

706
00:42:34,055 --> 00:42:37,591
- Phil, we have three hungry boys.

707
00:42:38,259 --> 00:42:41,562
You put all this pressure on
me to stretch a few dollars.

708
00:42:42,963 --> 00:42:45,366
It is embarrassing havin' a line

709
00:42:45,499 --> 00:42:47,701
of people behind me in
the grocery store waitin'

710
00:42:47,835 --> 00:42:50,971
for me to put stuff back
because I can't afford it.

711
00:42:51,105 --> 00:42:53,040
- It's fine.

712
00:42:53,174 --> 00:42:54,575
We're fine.

713
00:42:54,708 --> 00:42:56,677
The kids are fine.

714
00:42:59,747 --> 00:43:02,049
- I don't think we are, Phil.

715
00:43:06,587 --> 00:43:10,257
- Hm, I told you boys, I'm blessed.

716
00:43:10,391 --> 00:43:11,926
I cannot lose.

717
00:43:12,059 --> 00:43:13,961
- Jesus don't be playin' no dice.

718
00:43:14,095 --> 00:43:15,396
Only person who can play dice

719
00:43:15,530 --> 00:43:17,364
like that is the devil ,

720
00:43:18,132 --> 00:43:22,236
which will explain why you
riskin' your neck in this bar.

721
00:43:22,369 --> 00:43:23,437
- Hm.

722
00:43:24,071 --> 00:43:26,440
Nah, it's 'cause I like the
music and the company better.

723
00:43:26,575 --> 00:43:28,543
- Mm.
- If you went next door,

724
00:43:28,676 --> 00:43:30,845
you'd think they closed the
bar and opened up a morgue.

725
00:43:30,978 --> 00:43:33,380
- Really?

726
00:43:33,515 --> 00:43:36,350
Well, I heard that the
owners are lookin' to sell.

727
00:43:37,451 --> 00:43:38,352
- Really?

728
00:43:39,353 --> 00:43:42,524
Well, it just so happens
I'm in need of a job.

729
00:43:42,690 --> 00:43:45,493
- I said they were sellin',

730
00:43:45,626 --> 00:43:47,194
not hirin'.

731
00:43:49,564 --> 00:43:50,664
- They here now?

732
00:43:59,707 --> 00:44:01,108
Jim Perkins?

733
00:44:01,242 --> 00:44:02,143
- Yeah.

734
00:44:03,578 --> 00:44:04,613
- Phil Robertson.

735
00:44:04,745 --> 00:44:06,480
Nice to meet you.

736
00:44:06,615 --> 00:44:07,549
I heard y'all might be interested

737
00:44:07,681 --> 00:44:09,183
in doin' a little business.

738
00:44:10,251 --> 00:44:12,086
- What, you wanna buy the bar?

739
00:44:12,753 --> 00:44:13,921
- Well, thought we could talk about

740
00:44:14,054 --> 00:44:16,357
a bit more of a creative strategy.

741
00:44:19,326 --> 00:44:20,227
Hold on.

742
00:44:21,028 --> 00:44:22,730
Hold on.
- Phil!

743
00:44:26,767 --> 00:44:27,935
- Keep 'em closed.

744
00:44:30,070 --> 00:44:30,938
Come on.

745
00:44:31,071 --> 00:44:32,740
- Can I open them?
- Not yet.

746
00:44:33,908 --> 00:44:37,278
Just a little further, little further.

747
00:44:40,381 --> 00:44:41,849
Keep 'em closed.

748
00:44:44,752 --> 00:44:45,786
Stand here.

749
00:44:45,920 --> 00:44:47,788
Don't open 'em till I tell ya.

750
00:44:47,922 --> 00:44:49,658
- Why does it smell like urine?

751
00:44:54,695 --> 00:44:55,696
- Hold on.

752
00:44:58,567 --> 00:44:59,300
- Phil?

753
00:45:01,435 --> 00:45:02,937
- Okay, open 'em.

754
00:45:09,076 --> 00:45:12,614
- It's a bar.

755
00:45:15,816 --> 00:45:16,717
You bought a bar?

756
00:45:18,520 --> 00:45:19,486
- Sort of.

757
00:45:19,621 --> 00:45:22,624
- Phil, we can't afford a bar.

758
00:45:24,725 --> 00:45:27,394
I can't even afford groceries.

759
00:45:27,529 --> 00:45:28,963
- Don't worry about that.

760
00:45:29,830 --> 00:45:30,931
Look at this.

761
00:45:33,767 --> 00:45:36,770
This is a new start for us as a family.

762
00:45:36,904 --> 00:45:37,871
You been complainin' about money,

763
00:45:38,005 --> 00:45:40,207
we'll make some more money here.

764
00:45:40,341 --> 00:45:43,244
You been complainin' about
not spendin' time together,

765
00:45:43,377 --> 00:45:46,313
well, we'll all be here as a family.

766
00:45:48,782 --> 00:45:49,718
- I don't know, Phil.

767
00:45:49,850 --> 00:45:50,951
- Hey,

768
00:45:51,885 --> 00:45:53,254
I'll make it up to you.

769
00:45:55,624 --> 00:45:58,459
Kay, I'm gonna make it up to you.

770
00:46:00,160 --> 00:46:03,430
I know things didn't work
out with the teachin' job,

771
00:46:03,565 --> 00:46:04,932
and I was tired.

772
00:46:05,065 --> 00:46:07,569
I wasn't treatin' this family well.

773
00:46:09,970 --> 00:46:14,341
But this is a fresh start for
the Robertson family, okay?

774
00:46:15,276 --> 00:46:17,278
Alan and Jase, they can even help.

775
00:46:22,983 --> 00:46:26,420
- Look, I know you're a good man.

776
00:46:26,554 --> 00:46:27,988
I fell in love with that.

777
00:46:31,925 --> 00:46:34,028
But it's the drinkin'.

778
00:46:35,396 --> 00:46:38,198
How's bein' in a bar gonna help with tha

779
00:46:39,133 --> 00:46:42,570
- 'Cause I'll be workin', not drinkin'.

780
00:46:43,270 --> 00:46:47,509
Look, you'll keep an eye
on it, I'll keep on it.

781
00:46:50,077 --> 00:46:52,446
I'm gon' make this
work, I want it to work.

782
00:46:56,083 --> 00:46:59,353
You know you're the only one for me.

783
00:47:11,365 --> 00:47:12,333
I love you.

784
00:47:17,971 --> 00:47:22,976
- I love you.

785
00:47:23,110 --> 00:47:25,814
First thing we gotta do

786
00:47:25,946 --> 00:47:27,515
is get that pee smell outta here though,

787
00:47:27,649 --> 00:47:29,416
'cause that is horrible.

788
00:47:31,852 --> 00:47:32,953
- I agree.

789
00:47:33,087 --> 00:47:35,155
I thought I had it figured out (chuckles

790
00:47:36,156 --> 00:47:37,891
Finally I had arrived.

791
00:47:38,025 --> 00:47:39,694
A way to spend time with my family,

792
00:47:39,828 --> 00:47:42,129
makin' more money, and still get to hang

